---
import TechnologyLayout from '../../layouts/TechnologyLayout.astro';
import TextSection from '../../components/content/TextSection.astro';
import SectionWrapper from '../../components/ui/SectionWrapper.astro';
import WhenToChoose from '../../components/content/WhenToChoose.astro';
---

<TechnologyLayout
  title="Google Cloud Platform | Nimzo Data"
  description="We build exclusively on GCP — BigQuery, Dataform, Looker, Cloud Storage. Expert GCP data consulting for European companies."
  toolName="Google Cloud Platform"
  toolCategory="Cloud Platform"
  heroPositioning="We build exclusively on GCP — not because it's what we know, but because it's the right choice for European data teams that need compliance, global reach, and a best-in-class analytics stack."
>
  <TextSection title="What It Is" bg="white">
    <p>Google Cloud Platform is Google's suite of cloud computing services. For data work, it offers an integrated stack — from storage (Cloud Storage, BigQuery) to transformation (Dataform, Dataproc) to visualization (Looker) — all designed to work together without custom glue code.</p>
  </TextSection>

  <TextSection title="Why We Chose It" bg="white">
    <p>GCP's analytics stack is the most cohesive in the market. BigQuery alone changes how you think about data — serverless, fast, and economical at the right scale. The tight integration between services means less time debugging infrastructure and more time building value.</p>
  </TextSection>

  <TextSection title="How We Use It" bg="white">
    <ul class="how-list">
      <li>Design and provision GCP project architecture with proper IAM, VPC, and billing structure</li>
      <li>Configure BigQuery datasets, access controls, and cost governance (slot reservations, column-level security)</li>
      <li>Set up Cloud Composer (managed Airflow) or Cloud Workflows for orchestration</li>
      <li>Implement Cloud Storage lifecycle policies and data landing zones for ingestion pipelines</li>
      <li>Advise on GCP region selection for EU data residency requirements (GDPR compliance)</li>
    </ul>
  </TextSection>

  <SectionWrapper bg="white" py="lg">
    <WhenToChoose
      title="When GCP is the right choice — and when it isn't"
      intro="We're GCP-only, but that doesn't mean GCP is right for everyone."
      blocks={[
        {
          heading: 'Choose GCP when:',
          bullets: [
            'Your workload is analytics-heavy (BigQuery is the best value warehouse in the market)',
            'You need European data residency',
            "You're already in the Google ecosystem (Google Ads, GA4, Workspace)",
            'You want a cohesive stack with fewer moving parts',
          ],
        },
        {
          heading: 'Choose AWS when:',
          bullets: [
            "You're running complex multi-service applications with Lambda, SQS, DynamoDB, and the rest of the AWS-native stack",
            'You need deeper enterprise features',
          ],
        },
        {
          heading: 'Choose Azure when:',
          bullets: [
            'Your organization is heavily Microsoft-invested (M365, Power BI, AD)',
            'Data gravity is already on Azure',
          ],
        },
      ]}
      footer="Azure's data services work, but BigQuery is still the better warehouse."
    />
  </SectionWrapper>
</TechnologyLayout>

<style>
  .how-list {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 22px;
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .how-list li { margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .how-list li::marker { color: var(--color-primary); }
</style>
